title: Facebook Won't Let Australians Share Any News, If It's Forced To Share Revenue
text: Facebook Inc (NASDAQ: FB) said Monday it would have to “reluctantly” stop people in Australia from sharing local and international news on both its and subsidiary Instagram's social media platforms, should a draft law that mandates revenue sharing with news organizations come into effect.

title: Facebook threatens to block news in Australia if regulations are enacted
text: The social media giant argues that new rules altering the financial arrangement between publishers and online platforms could make it impossible to share news content.

title: Facebook Could Block Sharing of News Stories in Australia
text: The move, a response to pressure to pay publishers when their stories are posted on the social network, could add to internet silos springing up around the world.

title: Facebook partners with external researchers to study its impact during U.S. election
text: Facebook Inc said on Monday it is partnering with external researchers to examine the impact of the social media site on society during the 2020 U.S. presidential election.

title: Facebook VP Brian Boland, 11-year veteran with partnership focus, resigns
text: Brian Boland, who was vice president of partnerships product marketing, operations, partner engineers and analytics, announced his resignation from the company last week on Workplace, the company's internal social network.

title: 7 Hot Cloud Stocks to Buy Now For Long-Term Profits
text: The five U.S. Cloud Czars are now worth nearly $7 billion, and cloud stocks of all types have been delivering profits in 2020.

title: Facebook partially documents its content recommendation system
text: Algorithmic recommendation systems on social media sites like YouTube, Facebook and Twitter, have shouldered much of the blame for the spread of misinformation, propaganda, hate speech, conspiracy theories and other harmful content. title: Keep Buying Facebook Stock on the Dip for the Foreseeable Future
text: Long-term, I think Facebook is the next $1 trillion stock. Near-term, FB stock could move lower after becoming a bit overbought.

title: 10 Jefferies High-Conviction Stock Ideas for the Rest of 2020
text: With stocks at record highs, and top Wall Street strategists like Jefferies Sean Darby cautioning that perhaps we have moved into a “euphoria” stage, it makes sense for investors to not only exercise caution when selecting stocks but to manage what Darby terms as “draw-down” risk.
